BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:FYFRubmfa1dCTLLqIErkz
SUMMARY:Earth Month Event | Restoration at Homestead Park
DTSTAMP:20260406T054319Z
DTSTART:20260418T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us in Homestead Park where we will be removing common ivy 
	 and blackberry crowding native plants. This will be a great opportunity t
	o  learn the basics of restoration and plant identification\, all while ma
	king our local forests healthier. Come get your hands in the dirt\, work a
	longside neighbors and friends\, and eat snacks!\n\nNo experience necessar
	y all ages welcome\; gloves and tools are provided. Please note: we requir
	e participants aged 14 and under to volunteer with a parent or guardian at
	  a ratio of 1 adult to 3 kids.\n\nWhen:  Saturday\, April 18th\, 10am-1pm
	\n\nWhere: Homestead Field\, follow VOLUNTEER EVENT signs\n\nWhat to bring
	: Dress for the weather in clothes you don't mind getting dirty \\(think: 
	long p ants\, boots or sneakers\\). Bring a water bottle. Small snacks\, g
	loves\, and tools will be provided.\n\nRegistration: https://volunteersign
	up.org/RMPY L\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-month
